          <h3>1. Wrong Attestation Chain</h3>

          <p>
            The <a href="/services/attestation/">attestation chain</a> differs depending on your home country's relationship with the Hague Convention. Getting this wrong is the most expensive mistake because it requires restarting from your home country.
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Hague member countries</strong> (India, USA, UK, Philippines, Bangladesh, Canada): Your document needs notarization, then apostille from the relevant authority. The UAE accepts apostilles from these countries.</li>
            <li><strong>Non-Hague countries</strong> (Pakistan, Egypt): Your document needs notarization, then authentication by your home country's MOFA, then attestation by the UAE Embassy in your country. This is a longer chain with more steps.</li>
          </ul>

          <p>
            The UAE itself is <strong>not a Hague Convention member</strong>. Documents going from the UAE to other countries always require the full embassy attestation chain, regardless of the destination country's Hague status.
          </p>

          <h3>2. Missing or Incomplete Translation</h3>

          <p>
            <a href="/services/legal-translation/">MOJ-certified Arabic translation</a> is expected for all foreign-language documents. Common translation problems that trigger GDRFA rejections:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>No translation at all.</strong> Submitting documents only in English or another foreign language.</li>
            <li><strong>Non-MOJ translation.</strong> Using a certified translation from abroad (UK, Germany, or home country certified translators are not accepted). The translation must bear a UAE MOJ stamp.</li>
            <li><strong>Partial translation.</strong> Translating the main document but not the attestation stamps, notary seals, or handwritten annotations.</li>
            <li><strong>Translation before attestation.</strong> The translation does not reflect the attestation markings because it was done first.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3. Name Mismatches</h3>

