            <li><strong>Missing or incorrect translation:</strong> Get a new <a href="/services/legal-translation/">MOJ-certified translation</a> that captures all stamps and attestation markings.</li>
            <li><strong>Name mismatch:</strong> Request a translator's note clarifying the name variation. In some cases, a notarized affidavit of name equivalency from your home country may help.</li>
            <li><strong>Expired document:</strong> Obtain a fresh document and restart the attestation chain.</li>
            <li><strong>Missing document:</strong> Obtain and process the missing document through the full attestation-then-translation sequence.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Step 3: Resubmit Through the Typing Center</h3>

          <p>
            Return to the same typing center with your corrected documents. They will update your application in the GDRFA system. Resubmission fees may apply depending on the typing center.
          </p>
        </section>

