            Before visiting the typing center, run through this checklist:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Attestation chain complete?</strong> Every foreign document has the correct stamps for your country's Hague status. Check the <a href="/resources/attestation-guide/">attestation guide</a> for country-specific requirements.</li>
            <li><strong>MOFA stamp present?</strong> UAE MOFA attestation is the final step before translation.</li>
            <li><strong>MOJ-certified translation?</strong> Arabic translation bearing the UAE MOJ translator stamp. License number visible. Translation done after attestation.</li>
            <li><strong>Names match?</strong> Check every document against your passport. Flag any transliteration differences to your translator.</li>
            <li><strong>Documents current?</strong> Passport valid 6+ months. PCC within validity. Medical fitness within 60 days.</li>
